text.__SUMMARY__:
Eucalyptus yumbarrana, commonly known as the Yumbarra mallee is a mallee that is native to the south coast of South Australia.
The mallee tree is multi-stemmed typically growing to a height of 6 metres (20 ft) with rough, grey coloured, fibrous-stringy bark on the trunk and lower stems that becomes smooth, grey to cream above. Adult leaves are a glossy green colour that are 133 millimetres (5 in) long and 46 millimetres (2 in) wide with a lanceolate to broad-lanceolate shape.
